INSERT INTO `Notes` VALUES (3,'To increase music skills','Given a session, J. will demonstrate knowledge and learning on at least one page in the piano book','Given a session, J. will participate in active music making with MT for at least 5 minutes every session',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,17,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(6,'To increase music skills','Given a session, J. will demonstrate knowledge and learning on at least one page in the piano book','Given a session, J. will participate in active music making with MT for at least 5 minutes every session',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,11,2021,17,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Josiah was in the mood to play the piano right away. He described the Clair De Lune song he listened to last time as “old-school” which I thought was a fun alternative way to described classical music. He played two new songs from the performance book and finger isolation remained to be a challenge, but he got some good practice in regardless. ','document'),(13,'To increase music skills','Given a session, J. will demonstrate knowledge and learning on at least one page in the piano book','Given a session, J. will participate in active music making with MT for at least 5 minutes every session',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,18,11,2021,17,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"Hello\"','document'),(16,'To develop therapeutic rapport','Given a session, F. will musically engage with MT at least twice by mutual music making, playing together or active listening as evidenced by meaningful eye contact, for three consecutive sessions','Given a session, F. will verbally engage with MT by answering close-ended questions 3 out of 3 times and one A or B question for three consecutive sessions',' Given a session, F. will communicate to MT his intentions (asking for help/permission) verbally or gesturally at least once, for three consecutive sessions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,29,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(17,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,11,2021,29,'Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Felix requested the All About That Bass song in the car to mom so I honored that request in session. Felix nodded while smiling when I asked him to confirm. He picked out a couple of percussive instruments including a duck quacker while moving around and playing along with music. I asked him some open-ended questions such as what should be our next song, and what does the duck quacker sound like, but Felix didn’t answer them. He did answer all my close-ended questions sometimes with a smile and a big nod. He also answered a A or B question by saying the name of the song he’d rather listen to. Then we spent lots of time playing the ocean and gathering drum. Felix gradually started playing more freely and loudly as he liked with my encouragement. He was very interested the bead movement in the ocean drum and played the drum loudly so they could splash everywhere. ','document'),(18,'To improve self-calming Skills','Given a session, G will engage in deep breathing at least 4 times per session for 100% of the sessions.','When playing piano, G will slow down tempo for the remainder of the session after MTs verbal prompt',NULL,'To improve piano playing',' Given a piano song, G will learn to play it with accurate notes and a steady beat and perform it for two consecutive sessions','Given a piano song, G recognize the correct notes on the score without corrections ¾ times for 3 consecutive sessions',NULL,'To improve rate of speech and story comprehension through singing and playing piano','Given a piano song, G will learn to play and sing at the same time for the assigned part of the piece every week and sing in a volume audible by MT.','Given a session, G will demonstrate understanding of lyrics by showing movements that match the movements and answering questions correctly related to the song',NULL,19,11,NULL,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(19,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,11,2021,28,'N/A','No',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'No','N/A',NULL,'First','document'),(20,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,11,2021,28,'N/A','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','N/A',NULL,'Second','document'),(21,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,18,11,2021,28,'No','Yes',NULL,'No','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Third','document'),(22,'To increase engagement and mutual music making','Given a session, T. will demonstrate awareness of boundaries by sticking with only the instruments he picked out at the beginning of the session','Given a session, T. will musically engage with at least three different instruments for more than 30 seconds',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,31,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(23,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,31,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Teddy\'s number today was eight. We agreed to perform eight songs during the session and Teddy got out eight instruments of his choice. He did want to get more and I redirected him multiple times to stick with those he pulled out and actually play them instead of pulling more out. He didn\'t like Jingle Bells but was fine with some other Christmas songs. I was surprised to find that he seemed to know Ring of Fire and asked for it and we went back-and-forth singing It\'s beginning to look a lot like \'pajamas\' as made up by him.','document'),(24,'To improve communication skills','Given a session, T. will sing along to familiar songs for at least 5 times when prompted','Given a session, T. will verbally answer at least 3 questions independently either through singing or speaking, for 3 consecutive sessions','Given a session, T. will wait and follow musical/verbal prompt of “stop and go” while passing the ball back and forth with caregiver 8 out of 10 opportunities, for 3 consecutive sessions ','To decrease fixation and facilitate smoother transitions ','Given a session, with help of visual schedule, and/or sung transition prompts, T. will move onto the next intervention or stay with the current one with under 3 redirections for at least once during the session, for 3 consecutive sessions','iven a session, T. will follow deep breathing exercises with prompts at least 5 times breathing out and in',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,32,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(25,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,32,'Yes','N/A','N/A','Yes','N/A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We worked on bilateral movement and color recognition by having Tommy drum with two mallets today. I put down the colored visuals and lyrically prompted him to play with the instructed color repeatedly about 6 times. Tommy showed increased awareness of what color he was supposed to play at the end. He stayed patient with everything he was asked to do as well without getting frustrated and wanted to say goodbye.','document'),(26,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(27,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nate chose to play the guitar today even though the room we were in had multiple pianos just like last time. He suggested we play some Christmas music as it is December this month and request Mistletoe by Justin Bieber right away. After that, he tried to tell me about this artist whom I didn\'t know and later by talking to mom, I learned the name was Brad Paisley whom I still didn\'t know any songs from. We played a couple more December/Christmas related songs and Nate participated by humming and playing the guitar expressively','document'),(28,'To increase self-expression','Given a session, M. will play at least two songs on her guitar while singing','Given a session, M. will come up with at least 70% lyrics to fill in the song that addresses emotional regulation goals',NULL,'To increase coping strategies','Given a session, with the help and prompting of MT, M. will verbally identify a coping strategy that can be used in a difficult time','Given a session, M. will follow and stay with an experiential musical intervention that can be generalized to outside of sessions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,34,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(29,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,34,'Yes','N/A',NULL,'No','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Mary\'s reaction time was rather long today. She took a lot of time thinking about her decisions and responding to my questions and directions. She wanted to learn the piano, so we hopped on and improvised on the black keys for a bit. She said it was cool to do that but didn\'t expressively participate like she usually would. Then I put the stickers on the piano to help her learn chords and she tried it out for five minutes before wanting to quit due to difficulty and too high of expectation. She needed extra help and prompting when performing with the guitar reading chords from her Christmas book today as well.','document'),(30,' To improve piano playing','Given a session, I. will demonstrate increased accuracy playing the piano after gross motor intervention provided by MT','Given a sightreading exercise, I. will demonstrate an increase in accuracy while playing the piano and reading notes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,35,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(31,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,35,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Isaac was in a cheerful mood today. He took quite some time getting through the tougher exercises in the piano app. When he turned on the note name function, his accuracy significantly improved so it could be inferred that his inaccuracy is largely due to having to reading music and having that take up brain power allocated to moving his fingers. I told him that things will get tougher from here as he has reached the level in the app that matches his current level.','document'),(32,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,29,'Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Felix answered my open-ended question for the first time. I asked him what he was holding and he said “microphone”. He was also playing a handmade instrument from school before entering the room and mom told me that he would like to go by the name “Fe” from now on. We first played the gathering drum, aiming to play it so hard that his handmade instrument would flip upside down. Then we did some improvisation on various instruments he picked out as usual.','document'),(33,'To increase emotional regulation skills','Given a progressive muscle relaxation intervention, M. will complete stretches and deep breathing as prompted by MT','When M. shows signs of agitation, anxiety or anger upon entering the session, M. will choose a musical intervention to help with her emotions and stick through with the intervention','When M. shows signs of agitation, anxiety or anger upon entering the session, M. will be able to self-identify and report feeling so','To increase artistic expression','Given an isoprinciple-playlist-making intervention, M. will identify how a song makes her feel 2 out of 3 opportunities to add songs to the list','Given a session, M. will engage in active music making in at least 2 chosen forms (singing with digital device, songwriting, playing the piano, or improv) and verbally report how that made her feel every session',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,36,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(34,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,36,'Yes','N/A','N/A','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We started with some vocal warmups and deep breaths as suggested by Madelyn. Madelyn identified her emotions to be somewhere in the middle on the isoprinciple playlist spectrum by selecting the song in the middle to perform. She successfully navigated on her iPad app to our playlist easily and remembered the song Juice from two weeks ago and added that to the correct place in the playlist. We then talked about her thanksgiving experience. Madelyn said that she was happy when watching football game with family and got mad when she accidentally broke a vase on Sunday. Overall she described her break as good but pretty bad also. We concluded that maybe it was because it ended on a low note due to the broken vase on Sunday.','document'),(35,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(36,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We sang a variety of songs today including Here Comes Santa Claus, You’ve got a friend in Me, Beauty and the beast on the piano, and For the First Time in Forever the original version. Ella showed me a song that her choir was currently doing with singing and movements. She showed increased willingness and comfort level with reading lyrics in between music staves as well. ','document'),(37,'To increase flexibility and impulse control','Given a session, D. will perform a duet with MT by following the countdown and playing at a consistent tempo with MT for at least 1 time successfully, for 3 consecutive sessions',NULL,NULL,'To increase communication skills','Given a session, D. will initiate verbal conversation such as greeting or announcing what piece he is playing next, at least 3 times for 3 consecutive sessions ','Given a session, D. will independently answer MT’s question at least twice during a session, for 3 consecutive sessions',NULL,'To increase sight reading abilities','iven a session, G. will complete 1 page of sight reading melody with 80% accuracy the first two times for 3 consecutive sessions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(38,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,12,2021,38,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'No','No',NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'David was motivated to play a variety of Christmas songs as last time. He practiced Adeste Fideles over the break and played the whole song proficiently. I accompanied him on Christmas songs that were easier to play to keep him playing at a steady tempo. Among the songs he’d practiced before, it seemed that he needed some reviewing on Have Yourself a Merry Little Christmas as he requested to mark the score when it was already marked. This became his homework for this upcoming week. ','document'),(39,'To increase emotional expression and coping skills, and decrease anxiety as exhibited by active music making/songwriting to spoken response. ','Tyler will verbalize how music making makes him feel 2-3 times during the session unprompted','Tyler will verbalize one way of using music as a positive coping skill when prompted by MT-BC','Tyler will verbalize a decrease in anxiety from beginning of session to end of session when prompted by MT','To improve receptive understanding of music and physical musical skills as exhibited by utilization of singing / music making to spoken response and musical performance. ','Tyler will demonstrate understanding of musical concepts as seen through active music making','Tyler will verbalize understanding of musical concept when prompted by MT-BC.',NULL,'To increase utilization and strength in L hand (4 digits) as exhibited by active music making/instrument play.','Tyler will play 1 line of music with L hand on piano when prompted by MT','Tyler will play 1 line of music with L hand on guitar/piano unprompted',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,39,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,39,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,' Tyler met with me in-person today. He shared a mix of good and bad news regarding his grandpa’s health and how he was doing the past couple of weeks. When he was sitting in the hallway of the hospital, he wrote down a song about finding hope amidst suffering. He spent most of the session time trying to find melodies to go with the lyrics and realized he’d like to write something like Amazing Grace with a country style. We concluded that he could do two things while at home this week to work on this song: determine which country chords he’d like for this song and work on very small sections at a time, record either by writing it down or recording on the phone before moving onto the next small section.','document'),(41,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(42,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,12,2021,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We started with a small group and the group grew a bit larger over time. We moved to Hands are for clapping and shivery shakey blues working on body percussion, coordination and body parts identification. Then through boomlearning cards on the screen, we worked on numbering sequence and counting through stories about sea animals. ','document'),(43,'To make this work','Hello',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,41,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(44,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,12,2021,41,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'sgapsghphgpbpdufpbaupgaugpjopjg','document'),(45,'To improve communication','Given a session, Joe will complete task 3 out of 3 opportunities',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,41,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(46,'To improve communication','Given a session, Joe will demonstrate increased ability to say hello',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,43,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(47,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,12,2021,43,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'gasigpainpaf','document'),(48,'To increase music skills','Given a session, J. will demonstrate knowledge and learning on at least one page in the piano book','Given a session, J. will participate in active music making with MT for at least 5 minutes every session',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,12,2021,17,'N/A','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We played a rhythm game to start and Josiah enjoyed the challenge of it. He played both guitar and piano freestyle afterwards.','document'),(49,'To improve sustained attention','Given a session, T. will sustain engagement with an instrument playing/singing intervention for at least 30 seconds without verbal redirections from parents or MT for 3 consecutive sessions','Given a session, T. will sustain mutual music making with MT for at least 30 seconds for 3 consecutive session',NULL,'To improve fine motor skills ','Given a session, T. will engage in at least three fine motor movements independently with various instruments, for 3 consecutive sessions ',NULL,NULL,'To develop self-calming strategies','Given a session, T. will engage in deep breathing facilitated musically for at least 5 times, for 3 consecutive sessions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,44,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(50,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,12,2021,44,'No','Yes',NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'No',NULL,NULL,'Parvati appeared more anxious than her baseline today as evidenced by increased frequency of raised voices, not being able to sit still and take directions and verbalizing wanting Kacey and going home. I gave her opportunities to just listen to music and relax and asked her for her input for what to do next. She was fully engaged with the ocean drum as usual and used some of her favorites such as five little fishies to calm herself when getting upset. She didn\'t engage with things like the parachute or any other instruments.','document'),(51,'To improve piano playing','Given a session, A. will stay engaged with piano learning for at least 10 minutes','Given a session, A. will actively engage with music making on any instruments of his choice for at least 5 minutes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,45,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(52,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,12,2021,45,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aquinas was ready to learn piano right away and didn\'t carry any negative feelings with him from two weeks ago when he didn\'t want to play at all. He stayed engaged and focused throughout the lesson and showed progress on fingering choices and finger isolation and dexterity. We also briefly reviewed the concept of repeats as discussed last time and new concepts such as measures and bar lines.','document'),(53,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,5,12,2021,46,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(54,'To increase music skills','Given a session, J. will demonstrate knowledge and learning on at least two pages in the piano book','Given a session, J. will participate in active music making with MT for at least 5 minutes every session',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,5,12,2021,17,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(55,'To improve emotional regulation','Given a session, J. will identify her emotions and speak in full sentences such as “I feel (emotion)” when prompted verbally or musically for at least three times during every session','Given a session, J. will identify at least one coping strategies such as things that make her happy instead of answering “I don’t know”','Given a session, J. will actively participate in deep breathing and/or body movement that help with self regulation','To improve speech articulation','Given a session, J. will sing along to familiar songs by filling the blank of therapist’s singing for at least 3 times every session','Given a session and lyrics displayed on the screen, J. will independently sing at least 2 phrases on her own to a familiar song',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,6,12,2021,48,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(56,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,6,12,2021,48,'Yes','Yes','N/A','N/A','N/A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We continued our jeopardy game from last time. The computer remembered the scores but didn\'t remember which activity we had done previously. We used this as an opportunity to help Jodi review what she did last time. She didn\'t remember much and resorted to her default answer \"I don\'t know\" a lot but with some persistent reminding, she was able to figure it out. She picked a couple of body percussion activities in a row and it became increasingly easier for her to come up with a movement independently even though at first it took her a long time and she said she was scared to pick one.','document'),(57,'To improve self-calming Skills','Given a session, G will engage in deep breathing at least 4 times per session for 100% of the sessions.','When playing piano, G will slow down tempo for the remainder of the session after MTs verbal prompt',NULL,'To improve piano playing','Given a piano song, G will learn to play it with accurate notes and a steady beat and perform it for two consecutive sessions','Given a session, G will listen for feedback after playing and follow directions to retry sections and implement the feedback he was given twice a session',NULL,'To improve rate of speech and story comprehension through singing and playing piano','Given a piano song, G will learn to play and sing at the same time for the assigned part of the piece every week and sing in a volume audible by MT.','Given a session, G will demonstrate understanding of lyrics by showing movements that match the movements and answering questions correctly related to the song',NULL,6,12,2021,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(59,'To improve core strength and posture','Given a session, A. will follow gross motor movement facilitation with music 4 out of 5 times during a session that involves core movement and posture ',NULL,NULL,'To improve pincer grasping and finger isolation','Given a session, A. will follow fine motor movement facilitation with instrument play or ASL 4 out of 5 times during a session that involves pincer grasping and finger isolation',NULL,NULL,'To improve eye tracking and reading','Given a session, A. will complete at least 10 lines of lyric reading and play piano chords when independently reading lead sheet for at least a verse and a chorus',NULL,NULL,6,12,2021,54,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(60,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,6,12,2021,54,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Atku asked for Christmas songs and suggested Santa Tell Me. He did a mix of reading lyrics word-by-word, playing chords while reading independently, and doing so with my help of pointing to work on his eye tracking and fine motor skills. He had some trouble with completing movements that involved hopping on one feet and balance due to a lack of core strength.','document'),(61,'To improve self-advocacy and increase decision making exhibited by self-directed session order when given intervention choices and options. ','Hanna will choose the order of session within the 9-minute increments of the 45-minute session (5 interventions total)',' Hanna will engage in active music through instrument play of piano',' Hanna will take on a leadership role and make decisions throughout session regarding musical selections, instrumentation, turn taking, etc.',' To elevate mood and improve self-esteem and independence ','Hanna will verbalize how music making makes her feel 4-5x throughout session when prompted.','Hanna will verbalize how music making makes her feel 4-5x throughout session unprompted.',NULL,'To improve receptive understanding of music and physical musical skills as exhibited by utilization of singing / music making to spoken response and musical performance.','Hanna will verbalize understanding of musical concept when prompted by M','Hanna will verbalize understanding of 1 musical concept unprompted during session','Hanna will demonstrate understanding of musical concepts as seen through active music making',7,12,2021,55,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(62,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,55,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Hanna was very flexible regarding session format and due to snowy weather, we had our session on zoom today. Hanna had a smile on her face throughout the session and we were able to carry out almost everything we usually would have done in-person including movement warmup, singing, playing piano songs and analyzing them. Today Hanna picked out a couple of Christmas songs and sang and played at the same time.','document'),(63,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,56,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(64,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,57,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(65,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,58,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(66,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,56,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Preston was in a calm state today and picked a lot of Beatles songs upon watching the new Beatles movie on Disney plus.','document'),(67,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,58,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Devin wanted to talk about his trip to Disney and Universal today and expressed lots of excitement but also skepticism on his brother\'s choice on spending his thirtieth birthday in Orlando. He described his brother Austin to me for the first time as well. I encouraged him to still do some form of caroling this Christmas even though they couldn\'t do a full one without others\' help.','document'),(68,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,57,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wesley was in a pleasant mood today and we didn\'t talk about much about last time. He chose to dive straight into karaoke Christmas songs because he doesn\'t have much space in the basement. We chatted here and there about the songs and Wesley even went overtime singing the songs.','document'),(69,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,59,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(70,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,59,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Today\'s session took place online due to snowy weather. Abigail said she prefers in-person sessions but did well with the online format today. We went back-and-forth playing piano academy songs like the old times and she had a much easier time sticking with one thing than we are in-person. From the way her keyboard sounded, she was pressing the keys in an impatient manner a lot, which we can work on in the future.','document'),(71,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,12,2021,36,'Yes','N/A','N/A','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Madelyn was in a good mood today and said she liked humming during warmup from last time. After warmup, she intentionally picked songs to sing from the playlist and said that she felt very happy afterwards. We also played a rhythm game targeting at measuring Madelyn\'s threshold of tolerance of frustration. From my observation, her anxiety and frustration are not neurological as evidenced by not getting frustrated in the threshold game but more behavioral. This confirms that the behavioral approach we\'ve been taken on will likely help.','document'),(72,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,12,2021,60,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(73,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,12,2021,60,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' Teddy said that he would like more of a free-flow self-directed session structure for our time together. He first took interest in the violin and quickly figured out some ways to play it nicely without squeech-y sounds. He was investigative with all the instruments he played as last time including the gathering drum, drum set and marimba. He expressed that he really liked the percussion room and would like to explore that a bit more next time.','document'),(74,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,12,2021,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ella brought in her choir music and mom said the performance was a lot of fun and Ella was very excited about the music. She not only sang all her parts with harmonies while I played the other part mainly on the piano, she also showed me the movements. She picked a song from Zombies that was new as well.','document'),(75,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,12,2021,38,'N/A',NULL,NULL,'No','Yes',NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'David started playing the piano right away and I had to stop him and ask some greeting questions before. He practiced his homework very hard and did impressive work. For both adeste fiddles and Have Yourself a Merry Little Christmas, I instructed David to add the piano pedal as both of them have blocked chords that can sound segmented without the pedal. It took David a while to get the hang of pressing it but also releasing it every measure so it doesn\'t sound convoluted. ','document'),(76,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,12,2021,60,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Teddy brought in his saxophone today and swiftly put it together. He already figured out the majority of the fingering for the scale and how to consistently make the sound. He aimed for playing all notes in one breath which was overly challenging at times. We worked on the correct fingering for the scale as the top note actually is the second valve instead of open. Teddy was a bit confused on that but I also didn\'t push to let him have his space for exploration. He played the drum set for a bit at the end in the drum room and was very intrigued and invested as well.\r\n','document'),(77,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,9,12,2021,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We first listened to I Know a Chicken to shake shakers slowly, quickly, up and down and round and round. Then we talked about what we look forward to this holiday season and new year. Everyone had a chance to come up and tell me and we had some very creative answers to put back in the song for lyric rewrite. Then we did some Christmas singalong at the end.','document'),(78,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,9,12,2021,29,'Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Felix brought in his trombone he got as a gift for birthday. He tooted a couple times along with my piano playing. I asked him when his birthday was and he initially said I don\'t know but answered yes when I asked day by day. I invited him to sing along with me to the happy birthday song. He agreed to that and sang with a very whispered volume a couple of times.','document'),(79,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,9,12,2021,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nate suggested songs from Backstreet Boys and chose to stay on his guitar today. We did I Want it That Way and As Long As You Love Me which we agreed that got confusing with Justin Bieber\'s. Then he wanted to listen to a song that was stuck in his head by Ed Sheeran. I eventually figured out that it was Castle on the Hill after Nate sang a couple lines of melodies. We had a lot of fun playing that one.','document'),(80,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,9,12,2021,32,'Yes','No','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Tommy was quite focused to take a variety of directions today. He demonstrated ability to distinguish colors and to keep hitting the drum with the stick he was instructed to play. He also started singing whenever it was his turn when hearing the piano melody come on. It took him a long time to answer my A or B question today as he was hung up on the thought of telling dad something at the time.','document'),(81,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,9,12,2021,34,'N/A','N/A',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Mary wanted to sing a variety of Christmas songs today. She referenced her guitar book for song ideas and looked them up on youtube for karaoke tracks. She invited me to sing with her and I sang some harmonies here and there in addition to singing in unison. She concluded that she should write more songs of positive energy as one of her friends told her that revenge songs aren\'t productive.','document'),(82,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,9,12,2021,31,'Yes','No',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Teddy\'s number was 304 today but he didn\'t end up using that number for anything. He agreed to listening and singing to Christmas songs but became disengaged after about 3 songs. In order to engage him in a songwriting intervention, I asked him what he looked forward to in the holiday season or in the new year. I asked repeatedly and never got an answer. He described himself as \"frozen\" later and wanted to be done afterwards. ','document'),(83,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,9,12,2021,35,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Isaac first walked around the room to help himself regulate. Then he did fairly well when playing from sheet music. I played with him a big and he learned to use the piano pedal from me. We rotated between holiday tunes and regular lessons on the app. His accuracy improved from last time. He got frustrated when playing some challenging holiday tunes that ran very fast. I told him to turn on the letter note names to help and that worked well.','document'),(84,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,11,12,2021,45,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aquinas was ready to get playing right away when mom and I were conversing. He reviewed a couple of songs from last time and the rate at which he picked things up were faster than the last review. We reviewed the concept of measures and learned another song with the measure notation. Aquinas needed occasional reminders about keeping the correct rhythm and his recall of which note is how long needs some more reinforcements and reviews.','document'),(85,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,11,12,2021,44,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'No',NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Parvati had a much calmer body today and showed decreased amount of raised voices overtime. We started with some Christmas songs and nursery rhymes and Parvati did well with singing for half of them. I encouraged her to jump around in the room to dissipate some of her energy. She was bit more adamant on playing the ocean drum in a loud way likely for sensory needs so I let her do that without demanding quietness at all times. She was especially focused and engaged when we were reading books. She wanted me to put an arm around her shoulder while reading and read every word I pointed that was at her level and sang along.','document'),(86,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,11,12,2021,17,'No','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Josiah was 18 minutes late for the session due to having to trudge through heavy snow, so we kept going until the next client showed up for an additional 8 minutes. I gave him the report to take home. He wasn\'t in the mood to actively make music today and when I prompted him to show me he hadn\'t forgotten what he\'d learned, he did it successfully but impatiently. He improvised on the piano for a while. I asked him where he saw himself in music lessons in 2022. He said that he\'d like to learn more like reading music. ','document'),(87,'To improve rhythm',' Given the blue wool snare solo, E. will play the rhythms correctly taught in session for at least once with 100% accuracy in the unit of one system ','Given a combination worksheet, E. will warm up with correct R and L hands with only one correction from MT for 3 consecutive sessions',NULL,'To maintain calmness when playing percussion','Given a session, E. will take deep breaths when getting frustrated, and/or hold off playing the drum and ask for clarification or chant',NULL,NULL,'To improve saxophone playing','Given a session, E. will learn the order of putting together and taking apart the saxophone','Given a session, E. will demonstrate good breath support by following breathing exercises facilitated by MT at least 3 times','Given a session, E. will place his fingers at the right valves for the major scale',13,12,2021,61,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(88,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,12,2021,61,'No','N/A',NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'N/A','N/A','N/A','Eson missed his lessons the past couple times due to various reasons and showed up today. He looked like he had some anxiety which he verbally confirmed. To work on rhythm and neurological functions, we worked on drumming rhythm with one designated rest. He struggled with this a lot, not realizing when to rest and that he needs to play two eighth notes on the third beat. He showed improvement after repetitions but showed inconsistent memory recall on the rhythms we had learned before. I encouraged him to reflect on if his anxiety increased or decreased after our lesson even though he said he didn\'t know.','document'),(89,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,12,2021,62,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(90,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,12,2021,62,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Evan started exploring Dreams on the bass and was very intrigued and challenged by it at the same time. We pulled up a YouTube video with five-line staff to work on it, and figured out notes together. I gave some suggestions corrections regarding finger placement and by the end of it, Evan was able to play the first two lines of the melody with two variations. I emphasized that we were playing it at a rather fast tempo and that\'s why he thought it didn\'t sound as good, and that we could always take it slow but I had no doubt that he would master it eventually.','document'),(91,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,12,2021,28,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Gabe expressed his excitement towards coming back in-person in the spring and played through his homework with all the repeats with a steady tempo. He even suggested doing our warmup when I almost forgot. He picked I Feel Pretty for the next song to play and this song at first glance looks quite intimidating. Gabe stayed very patient with that and said the difficulty level is manageable. We made a homework plan to accommodate his travel plans to FL.\r\n','document'),(92,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,12,2021,46,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Piper looked disgruntled upon entering the room at first. She didn\'t say much about it and went ahead and started practicing her left hand skills with the app. She got frustrated at times when it was challenging but regulated herself back down after a while consistently. I offered some positive reinforcement pointing out that at times it was the app\'s fault. After finishing the practice, she looked more pleased and opened up about her newest liking to vocaloid and showed me a video of what it was.','document'),(93,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,12,2021,54,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Atku was in a pleasant mood and requested that we play some Christmas songs right away. He was more into singing today and we sang four to five songs in a row. I asked him to sing me the lyrics word for word and asked him to play chords at times. Then we used the hula hoop to work on his core. His reps and skills are increasing. His ability to jump with one leg over the hoop also improved from last time.','document'),(94,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,14,12,2021,55,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes','Yes','We had a joyful conversation about holiday plans and my newly bought Christmas tree and then we proceeded with movement to Life is a Highway. On the piano, we kept working on Can You Feel the Love Tonight and Hanna got through another chorus. She marked down notes to help her sight read and I realized we could do some more learning on the system above the five staff lines to help Hanna read those notes beyond the staff lines that she usually would\'ve relied on mnemonics. She told me about her absence next week due to holiday traveling plans as well.','document'),(95,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,14,12,2021,59,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Due to transportation issues, Abigail had her lesson online today. We started with some Christmas themed rhythm exercises using body percussion and her knowledge of quarter, eighth notes and rests. Then we took turns to play on the piano and she was engaged throughout the session on the other end.','document'),(96,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,14,12,2021,63,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(97,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,14,12,2021,63,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Due to new covid guidelines at MORA, we had three ladies Jessica, Sarah, and Amy from the same house in-person with me and Megan, Justin, and Terrie online from the same house. We took some time to set up the technology and it worked great. I was able to face directly at the camera and the in-person participants, and audio was loud enough for everybody and the visuals were there on the screen for all. I introduced everybody to the Little Drummer Boy, playing the pattern that corresponds to the lyrics and for those who were more comfortable, playing the the drum beats as accompaniment.','document'),(98,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,12,2021,39,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Tyler seemed to be in a good mood and reported some updated on his grandpa and his own well-being. We chatted about the weather, traveling and the hospital atmosphere before working on the piano music. We tackled three Christmas songs on the piano. Tyler took pictures of the score and sent them to me via email so I could give him pointers and help him with questions. It was a very productive session as we worked through some hard spots and perfected them in the songs.','document'),(99,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,12,2021,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Our session took place online today due to severe weather. Ella dressed in her costume and was ready to go. She picked a variety of songs including one from Monsters Inc that had a very interactive duet. I didn\'t know the song before but sang along to the best of my ability and had a lot of fun. ','document'),(100,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,15,12,2021,38,'N/A',NULL,NULL,'No','No',NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Our session took place online today due to severe weather. David had dad help redirect at the beginning of the session but it was hard to get a lot of directions across such as \"let\'s sing while playing\", and \"let\'s play softer\". After some repeated prompting, David started singing the lyrics and played softer. David did have a higher continuation rate, and almost never stopped playing and consistently announced the piece he decided to play next.','document'),(101,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,12,2021,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Due to school\'s lockdown drill, we began the session ten minutes late and some more students joined after a bit too. We moved our body and shook it off to Shivery Shakey Blues to help students move around after a confined lockdown. And then we took Christmas song requests from them and sang along. I ended the session with a relaxation/grounding exercise that involved mindfulness, sensory engagement, singing, and deep breathing.','document'),(102,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,12,2021,29,'Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We started with a Jingle Bell song with mutual music making as Fee picked out the desk bells first. Then I added some instructions and structure to the session by having Fee copying my rhythm. Conceptually, he had no problem doing that but he seemed to be caught off guard slightly as this was the first time us adding structure to the session. I played a Sleight Ride song that had these rhythmic exercises in it and demonstrated on the drum he picked out for me. Then Fee got interested in an electric bass CD even though we didn\'t end up getting it to play on the computer.','document'),(103,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,12,2021,35,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Isaac made no mistake on notes when playing his sheet music today. To help him increase accuracy and success rate, he turned on the note names and slowed down the tempo to some holiday songs. He was particularly into the Little Dreidel song and All I Want For Christmas Is You','document'),(104,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,12,2021,31,'Yes','No',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We started playing the boomwhackers and Teddy engaged with them for about 10 minutes. He wasn\'t interested in checking out the songs we were able to produce with the instruments as usual but treating them more like toys and objects for his taking. He then asked me to play a Christmas song but didn\'t engage much either. After some prompting, we settled for conversations about his family and his friend Declan. ','document'),(105,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,12,2021,34,'N/A','N/A',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Mary called me a day ahead to tell me that she would like her session online. During the session, she reiterated that she should write more positive songs and she would like to write one soon but just not today again. She instead sang through a variety of Christmas carols while I shared screen and lyrics.','document'),(106,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,12,2021,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nate agreed to start with Castle on the Hill by Ed Sheeran that we enjoyed playing last time. Then we checked out Supermarket Flowers by Ed Sheeran and realized it was about his mom passing away. We shared some of our perspectives on grief of the loved ones and proceeded with another song of a similar theme, Drops of Jupiter, and compared two songs\' narratives and perspectives on their mom\'s passing.','document'),(107,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,12,2021,32,'Yes','Yes','Yes','No','N/A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Tommy was very vocal and in a happy mood today. His volume was raised and went for the piano and started playing right away. He completed various tasks such as turn taking with singing and matching colors with boomwhackers. He wasn\'t as focused when it came to color matching as last time likely due to his higher energy and being in a more aroused state, but he did great with all the Christmas carol singing and kept playing the piano while singing. He was challenged to multi-task as well when being told what to do in the hello song while playing the piano.','document'),(108,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,6,12,2021,28,'N/A','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','N/A',NULL,'Gabe got a bit frustrated when being asked to follow the metronome and play his homework again at the beginning as well as during the lesson. Today we specifically focused on having Gabe listen for my feedback after his playing as he usually likes to quickly move onto his own agenda. He appreciated the body percussion warmup but needed a lot of reminder to actually do the body percussion instead of just watching and getting excited. I sent over two options for the next song to mom for them to decide what to play next week.','document'),(109,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,12,2021,62,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We went through and reviewed Smells Like Teen Spirit and Evan quickly picked up everything and played everything consistently with a steady tempo. Then we tried to find the pattern of Dreams together in the into and the first verse. I suggested he write it down on a sheet of paper with ways that make sense to him to help future memory recollection. And I will try to find a copy of the PDF to help with that too.','document'),(110,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,12,2021,61,'N/A','N/A',NULL,'N/A',NULL,NULL,'Yes','Yes','N/A','Eson looked to be in a state of anxiety upon entering the room. He had trouble putting together his saxophone with shaky and unsteady hands. I guided him through this process focusing on taking one step at a time. And then I asked him to use playing saxophone as an opportunity to practice deep breathing instead of focusing on the scale today. He needed repeated reminders to breathe deep but it got him to slow down a bit. At the end of the session after he put back the saxophone, he took a minute to close his eyes and relaxed for five minutes and reported feeling slightly better.','document'),(111,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,12,2021,48,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'I was told by Amy and confirmed by Celia that Jodi\'s speech had become more and more unclear and reason could be behavioral. She was not happy to go back to Speech Therapy and she said it had been rough for her. Her speech was very blurred at the onset of the session and I gave her plenty of opportunities to sing along. At first, she was hesitant but by the end of the session, she successfully completed all singing and Q&A tasks and scored points in the jeopardy game. Her affect turned a lot brighter and volume increased as well.','document'),(112,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,18,12,2021,45,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Aquinas had his sister and mom observe in the session today. He was very focused at reviewing and learning songs. To bring on the Christmas spirit, Aquinas learned how to play Jingle Bell using letter notes and used that as a warmup for his five-finger position. At the end, he asked to do a quick round of drumming and was very happy to play the Beet song again.','document'),(113,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,18,12,2021,17,'Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'We worked on reading notes today as that was something Josiah said he would like to learn more on last time. It took him some time to fully get focused and prompt but he successfully understood the inner workings of reading treble clef notes by the end of the session and enjoyed the challenge.','document'),(114,'To improve piano playing','Given a session, J. will complete at least two new pages of the piano book as well as four pages of review',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,12,2021,64,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(115,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,12,2021,64,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Jeremiah completed multiple pages of review and remembered almost everything he learned previously and reviewed rhythm notation and repeat signs. He was quick to pick up notes on the piano and find all notes up and down the piano. He has a great sense of rhythm and was proficient at counting beats.','document'),(116,'To improve rhythm','Given a session, I. will be able to recall drum names without reminding 4 out of 5 drums','Given a session, I. will repeat various rhythms using body percussion following MT\'s lead','Given a session, I. will show body coordination with his drummer stance and match visuals to drum beats',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,12,2021,65,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(117,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,12,2021,65,'No','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Caregiver Linda observed in the session today. Isaac needed some reminders to recall the drum names taught to him previously. He stayed engaged with the rhythm exercise throughout and demonstrated ability to recall rhythms such as quarter and eighth notes. His body coordination at times was falling behind his cognitive processing during body percussion but that would get better over time. He was able to match visuals to drums and had 60% success rate. He got bored with the drums and played the piano for the last 7 minutes of the session.','document'),(118,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,12,2021,46,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Piper had symptoms of covid and thus stayed home and we had our session online. She wanted to play the music jeopardy game we had previously played and was open to whatever I had in store even if the songs were for older audiences. She participated fully in name-that-tune and singalongs.','document'),(119,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,21,12,2021,55,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes','Yes','We first played a Christmas carol name-that-tune game and Hanna was very good at it. We laughed about certain songs sounding similar and the dark lyrics in grandma got ran over by a reindeer. Then we worked on Can You Feel the Love Tonight on the piano and using the white board, we reviewed note reading on the bass clef. Hanna said it was a lot of information and challenging but she was understanding it to the best of her ability.','document'),(120,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,21,12,2021,56,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Preston was at his baseline today with minor agitation and he said it was because his brother Austin got the covid and he and everyone was just so done with this virus at this point. He picked out a variety of songs and ended on time to make it to his doctor appointment.','document'),(121,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,21,12,2021,58,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Devin told me about the horrible experience he had with his plane rides there and back to Florida. Then he asked if we could switch our lesson time to a different date and said he would strongly like to do that. I provided some considerations for that and we would keep each other updated. Then he asked me for some piano tips in hopes of getting an electric keyboard this Christmas.','document'),(122,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,21,12,2021,57,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wesley spent the session time telling me about the Florida trip. I learned that his girlfriend got sick but he stuck by her side and it was fine at the end. He told me about the scary dinosaur part of the park and said overall it was a good trip.','document'),(123,'To improve guitar playing','Given a session, A. will complete the lesson objective for every session','Given a session, A. will demonstrate improved sense of rhythm and ability to keep a steady and constant tempo after being prompted by MT','Given a session, A. will demonstrate finger dexterity and fast reflex on learning and switching in between chords and performing songs fingerstyle','To increase positive self-statements','Given a session, A. will have at least 3 positive self-statements unprompted','Given a session, A. will turn his originally negative statements to positive for at least once after being prompted by MT',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,12,2021,66,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(124,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,14,12,2021,66,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Alex had good memory recall on the newly learned A chord. We spent time practicing switching chords to various Chinese songs again and talked about the role of counseling in our lessons. Alex thought that my only job was to teach him music and not to help him with anxiety. I explained that I\'d like to help him talk it out so he could be ready to learn music. He also said that he thought music was supposed to help with anxiety and I explained not all the time, and it\'s okay at times that it doesn\'t help.','document'),(125,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,21,12,2021,66,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Alex needed some more practice on the A chord whenever transitioning into it when we played Jingle Bells. He was surprised to realized that he actually had all the chords he needed to play a majority of Christmas songs. He also learned the Am chord and we reviewed how to read chord charts again.','document'),(127,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,21,12,2021,63,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bucky was in person with me with staff Laura who helped Bucky tremendously with following instructions and gave him more opportunities to participate. Megan, Justin, Mallory, Jessica, Sarah, Amy and Sarah joined online. We jammed to a number of Christmas carols and at the end participants came up with ideas of preferred activities they liked from this year and we wrapped up with We Wish You a Merry Christmas.','document'),(128,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,22,12,2021,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Due to technical issues, we couldn\'t get on YouTube or any other streaming services after trying some options. We played all songs Ella requested on the piano and she did well with these adaptations we had to make. Ella was solid in all her parts as usual and was conversational about her last day of school.','document'),(129,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,22,12,2021,38,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'We ended up having our session online due to some miscommunication. We played name-that-tune game with Christmas songs back-and-forth. It took David some time to realize the rule of the game as it was such a switch up, and then he did very well with naming all the songs. Then I named the songs he played and asked him to confirm as well.','document'),(130,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,22,12,2021,60,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Teddy started with the percussion room right away and explored all percussive instruments in the room such as Timpani, xylophone, marimba, and the drum set. He had fun altering the notes of the timpani to play the first line of Twinkle Twinkle. Then he got on the violin and played for a while. He made occasional comments and questions regarding the instruments but explored mainly on his own.','document'),(131,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,1,2022,62,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Our session took place online. Through referencing the same digital score, Evan and I had no problem tracking where each other was at. Evan practiced playing through the first verse and chorus till the guitar solo. Even though he found the whole piece to be challenging at the beginning of the session, his played everything fluently and it seemed that he had practiced this over the break as well. We will tackle the guitar solo part next time.','document'),(132,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,1,2022,48,'No','No','Yes','Yes','No',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Jodi had extremely blurred speech as last time and extreme reluctance to verbally answer any questions. Celia told me that Jodi\'s speech session hadn\'t started yet either due to holiday. Jodi\'s affect was much brighter when singing along and moving her body to music but whenever we used these musical prompts to ask her questions, she would retrieve back. I facilitated some big stretches to physically open her up and she did relatively well with answering questions such as the weather, day of the week as a part of the routine of our greeting.','document'),(133,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,1,2022,46,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Piper was on vacation with mom but was in a crabby mood and chose to skip it for this week. Mom and I chatted about the current covid situation and updates.\r\n','document'),(134,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,1,2022,28,'Yes','No',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes',NULL,'Gabe didn\'t end up going to Florida but instead had some elevator rides. He attended school in-person for the first time in almost two years and said he felt proud of himself. His completed his homework with 100% accuracy and likely previewed the next part as he described it as 1 out of 10 difficulty. In turn, his frustration didn\'t come from difficulty of the piece but rather slowing down. He struggled particularly with the eighth notes that are grouped four in a row. Having him practice playing only eighth notes with the metronome helped a bit by behaviorally normalizing the tempo as telling him to slow down didn\'t work as well.','document'),(135,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,1,2022,54,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'We carried out our usual routine of singing and playing on the piano even though we were online. I couldn\'t hear what Atku was playing sometimes so I wasn\'t certain that he was playing the right chord but he was indeed playing from what I could see. To get in some movement that involves core strength, I showed Atku an interactive movement video. He seemed very motivated by all the visuals and interactions and responded correctly with movements such as jumping, skating, ducking, punching and grabbing. ','document'),(136,'To increase emotional and physical self-regulation as exhibited by presenting with calm body while engaging in active music making.​ ','McKayla will be able to self-regulate back to a calm body during transitional portions of session.',' McKayla will be able to self-regulate back to a calm body when engaging in a new music making','MacKayla will clean away the instruments/objects she was all done with previously before moving onto another activity ',' To improve self-advocacy and increase decision making exhibited by self-directed session order when given a visual menu of intervention choices and options.',' McKayla will initiate choices on what she’d like to do next without MT’s prompting','McKayla will participate in improvisational music making (piano, singing, etc.) with minimal prompting.','McKayla will engage in music making through singing and playing piano to music she has selected',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,1,2022,68,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(137,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,1,2022,68,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Our session took place online and this was McKayla\'s first online experience with Music Therapy. She stayed seated and focused the entire time, and was open to a bigger range of suggestions and directions I gave her than when we were in-person. We completed a variety of musical engagement exercises including singing, dancing, body percussion, rhythm learning, learning about musical coping strategies, etc through the forms of music jeopardy game and music videos. It was also my first time hearing McKayla sing because she had refused to sing in the past when we were in-person.','document'),(138,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,1,2022,55,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes','Yes',NULL,'Yes','Yes','Yes','Our session took place online today. Hanna and I chatted about our holiday break and our favorite Christmas gift. We both had a wonderful time and were doing well. Hanna wanted to play songs from her worship song book, so we played the name-that-tune game again but this time with me guessing the songs. I had 50% success rate and Hanna did a good job at giving me hints just enough to help me and make it challenging. She enjoyed this game and was singing and playing the piano at the same time to give me hints.','document'),(139,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,1,2022,59,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Abigail and I chatted about our holiday breaks and covid here and there throughout the session and took turns on playing with piano academy. She kept pressing different buttons on the piano that resulted in the piano changing its keys and she kept scoring zero stars from that. I was confused too as it sounded like she was playing all the wrong notes. After realizing that, I reminded her to restart the piano whenever she keeps getting zero stars.','document'),(148,'To increase flexibility and impulse control','Given a session, D. will perform a duet with MT by following the countdown and playing at a consistent tempo with MT for at least 1 time successfully, for 3 consecutive sessions',NULL,NULL,'To increase communication skills','Given a session, D. will initiate verbal conversation such as greeting or announcing what piece he is playing next, at least 3 times for 3 consecutive sessions ','Given a session, D. will independently answer MT’s question at least twice during a session, for 3 consecutive sessions',NULL,'To increase sight reading abilities','Given a session, D. will complete 1 page of sight reading melody with 80% accuracy the first two times for 3 consecutive sessions',NULL,NULL,5,1,2022,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(149,'To improve self-regulation','Given a session, M. will follow deep breathing 3 out of 5 times when prompted musically',NULL,NULL,'To decrease impulsivity ','Given a session, M. will stop as musically directed when playing an instrument','Given a session, M. will play only one instrument at a time and be all done with past instruments 3 out of 5 times',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,5,2022,69,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'goals'),(150,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,5,1,2021,69,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Yes','No',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Our session took place online today. Mom was with Maggie for most of the session, helping prompt her to follow directions. Maggie did well with breathing out and following body movements given musical prompts, and had difficulty breathing in and sticking with an instrument for more than 5 seconds before her mind drifting to something else. She also became slightly fixated on subjects her mind drifted off to at times and it was hard to redirect her attention.','document'),(151,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,1,2022,63,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Our session took place online today. It was easier to hear everyone\'s voices even though harder to see everyone\'s faces with the online platform. Megan said that she prefers doing it fully online for various reasons. We chatted extensively about our holiday break and our resolutions, tried a new call-and-response rhythmic exercise and drummed along to new-year-themed music.','document'),(154,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,5,1,2022,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Our session took place online. Ella wore Merida\'s dress from Brave. She told me she got lots of DVDs of shows she likes such as Thomas the Engine for Christmas, and she spent Christmas Day at her grandma\'s house and had OJ and pancakes. She picked out songs from various Disney movies and we chose the ones with the movie scene in it as Ella knows all the lyrics to her songs as usual. I recommended her a YouTube video that facilitates interactive movement and played 10 seconds of it but it wasn\'t Ella\'s cup of tea.','document'),(155,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,5,1,2022,38,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'No','No',NULL,'Yes',NULL,NULL,'Dad and I chatted about recent covid situation and learned that covid is going around everywhere right now. I added some interaction and exercises from the past into the session and this threw off David\'s routine a bit. It took several prompts for him to understand what I was asking him, and he especially struggled with continuing playing the melody instead of repeating. Bringing these exercises back will hopefully re-train his ability to take directions and increase his flexibility with session flow.','document'),(156,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,6,1,2022,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Despite recent rising cases of covid, the classroom looked just as usual with about 7 students and multiple teachers. The students were ready to go and attentive. We did two songs in the theme of cold winter working on breathing and body part identification. Then everybody stood up and jumped around with an interactive video and then we ended the session with a calming song.','document');
